<paragraph id="5C43195D9430563F4FA86851FBA454E7" blockId="0.[136,1452,1148,1867]" box="[136,1039,1148,1175]" pageId="0" pageNumber="255">
<heading id="070BAE319430563F4FA86851FBA454E7" bold="true" box="[136,1039,1148,1175]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="0" pageNumber="255" reason="1">
<emphasis id="6E88C54F9430563F4FA86851FBA454E7" bold="true" box="[136,1039,1148,1175]" pageId="0" pageNumber="255">
<taxonomicName id="9BFC62DE9430563F4FA86851FEAF54E6" authorityName="Adanson" authorityYear="1763" box="[136,260,1148,1175]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Kalanchoe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="0" pageNumber="255" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="6E88C54F9430563F4FA86851FEAF54E6" bold="true" box="[136,260,1148,1175]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="255">Kalanchoe</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
[subg. 
<taxonomicName id="9BFC62DE9430563F4E7B6851FE5954E6" box="[347,498,1148,1175]" class="Gymnostomatea" family="Spathidiidae" genus="Bryophyllum" kingdom="Chromista" order="Spathidiida" pageId="0" pageNumber="255" phylum="Ciliophora" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="6E88C54F9430563F4E7B6851FE5954E6" bold="true" box="[347,498,1148,1175]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="255">Bryophyllum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
] sect. 
<emphasis id="6E88C54F9430563F4D1D6851FD2354E6" bold="true" box="[573,648,1148,1175]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="255">Alatae</emphasis>
elevated to the rank of subgenus
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5C43195D9430563F4FA8688CFCA15532" blockId="0.[136,1452,1148,1867]" pageId="0" pageNumber="255">
Throughout Raymond-Hamet’s long involvement in the taxonomy of 
<taxonomicName id="9BFC62DE9430563F4C51688CFC4E54C8" authorityName="Adanson" authorityYear="1763" box="[881,997,1185,1209]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Kalanchoe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="0" pageNumber="255" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="6E88C54F9430563F4C51688CFC4E54C8" box="[881,997,1185,1209]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="255">Kalanchoe</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the 20 
<superScript id="AB89B4159430563F4B6A68B2FBFD54DC" attach="left" box="[1098,1110,1183,1197]" fontSize="6" pageId="0" pageNumber="255">th</superScript>
century (
<bibRefCitation id="386D64AC9430563F4B9B688CFAE154C8" author="Smith, G. F." box="[1211,1354,1185,1209]" pageId="0" pageNumber="255" pagination="120 - 140" refId="ref2659" refString="Smith, G. F. (2020 b) The kalanchoes (Crassulaceae subfam. Kalanchooideae) of Raymond-Hamet (1890 - 1972). Bradleya 38: 120 - 140. https: // doi. org / 10.25223 / brad. n 38.2020. a 15" type="journal article" year="2020">Smith 2020b</bibRefCitation>
), 
<emphasis id="6E88C54F9430563F4A7C688CFADE54C9" box="[1372,1397,1185,1208]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="255">K.</emphasis>
sect. 
<emphasis id="6E88C54F9430563F4FA868EEFF6554AA" box="[136,206,1219,1243]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="255">Alatae</emphasis>
was the only infrageneric “groupe” for which he published a name (Raymond-Hamet 1933). All the other units he recognised were furnished with numbers only, a classification he adhered to even when producing one of the first illustrated works (Raymond-Hamet &amp; 
<bibRefCitation id="386D64AC9430563F4E916924FD4E5550" author="Marnier-Lapostolle, J." box="[433,741,1289,1313]" pageId="0" pageNumber="255" pagination="1 - 110" refId="ref2470" refString="Raymond-Hamet &amp; Marnier-Lapostolle, J. (1964) Le genre Kalanchoe au Jardin Botanique &quot; Les Cedres &quot;. Archives du Museum National d'Histoire Natural Septieme Serie, Tome VIII: 1 - 110; Plates I - XXXVII." type="journal article" year="1964">Marnier-Lapostolle 1964: 93</bibRefCitation>
) on a part of the genus some 60 years after having started his work on 
<taxonomicName id="9BFC62DE9430563F4F896906FEB65532" authorityName="Adanson" authorityYear="1763" box="[169,285,1323,1347]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Kalanchoe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="0" pageNumber="255" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="6E88C54F9430563F4F896906FEB65532" box="[169,285,1323,1347]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="255">Kalanchoe</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the early 1900s (
<bibRefCitation id="386D64AC9430563F4ED06906FDDC5532" author="Hamet, R." box="[496,631,1323,1347]" pageId="0" pageNumber="255" pagination="109 - 111" refId="ref2195" refString="Hamet, R. (1906 [Janvier - Mars). Note sur une nouvelle espece de Kalanchoe [Kalanchoe vantieghemii, as ' Van Tieghemi ']. Journal de Botanique [Morot] XX [20 e [annee] (No 1 - 3)]: 109 - 111. [https: // www. biodiversitylibrary. org / item / 22106  page / 113 / mode / 1 up]" type="book chapter" year="1906">Hamet 1906</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="386D64AC9430563F4DA26906FD115532" author="Hamet, R." box="[642,698,1323,1347]" pageId="0" pageNumber="255" pagination="869 - 900" refId="ref2273" refString="Hamet, R. (1907) Monographie du genre Kalanchoe. Bulletin de l'Herbier Boissier, ser. 2, 7: 869 - 900." type="journal article" year="1907">1907</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="386D64AC9430563F4DE56906FD555532" author="Hamet, R." box="[709,766,1323,1347]" pageId="0" pageNumber="255" pagination="17 - 48" refId="ref2300" refString="Hamet, R. (1908) Monographie du genre Kalanchoe. Suite et fin. Bulletin de l'Herbier Boissier, ser. 2, 8: 17 - 48." type="journal article" year="1908">1908</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="14E64AD69430563F4F9D6963FC3C573A" pageId="0" pageNumber="255" type="description">
<paragraph id="5C43195D9430563F4F9D6963FDCF5629" blockId="0.[136,1452,1148,1867]" pageId="0" pageNumber="255">
In the case of two species that are endemic to 
<collectingCountry id="24EB59CD9430563F4D856963FC835517" box="[677,808,1358,1382]" name="Madagascar" pageId="0" pageNumber="255">Madagascar</collectingCountry>
, namely 
<taxonomicName id="9BFC62DE9430563F4CA76962FF1255F8" authority="(Baker 1883: 142) Baillon (1885: 469)" authorityName="Baillon" authorityPageNumber="469" authorityYear="1885" baseAuthorityName="Baker" baseAuthorityPageNumber="142" baseAuthorityYear="1883" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Kalanchoe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="0" pageNumber="255" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="porphyrocalyx">
<emphasis id="6E88C54F9430563F4CA76962FBEA5517" box="[903,1089,1358,1382]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="255">K. porphyrocalyx</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="386D64AC9430563F4B6E6963FAA95517" author="Baker, J. G." box="[1102,1282,1358,1382]" pageId="0" pageNumber="255" pagination="87 - 158" refId="ref1880" refString="Baker, J. G. (1883 [1884 published 24 March 1883]) Contributions to the flora of Madagascar. - Part I. Polypetalae [Plates XXII &amp; XXIII]. Journal of the Linnean Society, Botany (London) 20 (126): 87 - 158. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1095 - 8339.1883. tb 00195. x" type="journal article" year="1883">Baker 1883: 142</bibRefCitation>
) 
<bibRefCitation id="386D64AC9430563F4A316963FF1255F8" author="Baillon, M. H." pageId="0" pageNumber="255" pagination="465 - 472" refId="ref1729" refString="Baillon, M. H. (1885 [seance du 18 fevrier]) Liste des plantes de Madagascar (suite de la page 464). [Kalanchoe § Kitchingia]. Bulletin Mensuel de la Societe Linneenne de Paris (Paris) 1 (59): 465 - 472. [https: // www. biodiversitylibrary. org / item / 41447  page / 60 / mode / 1 up]" type="journal article" year="1885">Baillon (1885: 469)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="C4C705D89430563F4FEA695CFEA155F8" box="[202,266,1393,1417]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[136,240,1174,1198]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,190,1152]" captionTargetId="figure-18@1.[151,1436,190,1152]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. Kalanchoe porphyrocalyx. A. K. porphyrocalyx var. porphyrocalyx growing epiphytically in habitat in the Andringitra Massif, southern Madagascar. B. K. porphyrocalyx var. sambiranensis in cultivation in South Africa. C. K. porphyrocalyx var. porphyrocalyx growing epiphytically in habitat in Andasihisatra, east of Anjozorobe, central Madagascar. D–E. K. porphyrocalyx var. porphyrocalyx in cultivation in Madagascar, with a close up (E) of the sparsely hairy flowers. Photographs: A. Joël Jacq; B. Gideon F. Smith; C. Nadia Raheliarisoa; D–E. David-Paul Klein." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5426198" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5426198/files/figure.png" pageId="0" pageNumber="255">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
) and 
<taxonomicName id="9BFC62DE9430563F4E6C695CFCF355F9" authority="(Stapf 1908: 258) Hamet (1910: 52)" authorityName="Hamet" authorityPageNumber="52" authorityYear="1910" baseAuthorityName="Stapf" baseAuthorityPageNumber="258" baseAuthorityYear="1908" box="[332,856,1392,1417]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Kalanchoe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="0" pageNumber="255" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="uniflora">
<emphasis id="6E88C54F9430563F4E6C695CFE6855F8" box="[332,451,1393,1417]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="255">K. uniflora</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="386D64AC9430563F4EF3695CFD2E55F9" author="Stapf, O." box="[467,645,1392,1417]" pageId="0" pageNumber="255" pagination="258 - 259" refId="ref2967" refString="Stapf, O. (1908) 943. Kitchingia uniflora Stapf [Crassulaceae]. In: XXXIV. Diagnoses africanae: XXIII, pp. 257 - 262. Bulletin of Miscellaneous Information, Royal Gardens, Kew 1908 (6): 258 - 259. [https: // www. biodiversitylibrary. org / page / 11624747  page / 265 / mode / 1 up]" type="journal article" year="1908">Stapf 1908: 258</bibRefCitation>
) 
<bibRefCitation id="386D64AC9430563F4DB5695CFCF355F9" author="Hamet, R." box="[661,856,1392,1417]" pageId="0" pageNumber="255" pagination="49 - 54" refId="ref2331" refString="Hamet, R. (1910 [Janvier]) Sur quelques Kalanchoe peu connus (Suite). Bulletin de la Societe Botanique de France [Tome Cinquante- Septieme], Quatrieme serie - Tome X) Quatrieme series 57: 49 - 54. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 00378941.1910.10832165" type="book chapter" year="1910">Hamet (1910: 52)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="C4C705D89430563F4C48695CFC0055F8" box="[872,939,1393,1417]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="2.[136,240,1208,1232]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,350,1183]" captionTargetId="figure-89@2.[151,1436,350,1183]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 2. Kalanchoe uniflora. A–D. K. uniflora growing epiphytically in habitat in Parc National de Montagne d’Ambre at 1000 m above sea level, northern Madagascar. E. The winged seeds, sparsely hairy pedicel, calyx, and attenuated carpels of K. uniflora. F. Plant in cultivation in South Africa. Photographs: A–D. David-Paul Klein; E. Ronen Shtein; F. Gideon F. Smith." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5426200" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5426200/files/figure.png" pageId="0" pageNumber="255">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
), Raymond-Hamet (1933) argued that they are closely related, a view with which we agree, and included them in 
<emphasis id="6E88C54F9430563F4C5E69B9FC3B55DA" box="[894,912,1428,1451]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="255">K</emphasis>
. sect. 
<emphasis id="6E88C54F9430563F4CFC69BEFB8955DA" box="[988,1058,1427,1451]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="255">Alatae</emphasis>
. Raymond-Hamet (1933: 547–548) described 
<emphasis id="6E88C54F9430563F4FD4699AFEA655BF" box="[244,269,1463,1486]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="255">K.</emphasis>
sect. 
<emphasis id="6E88C54F9430563F4E68699BFE2555BF" box="[328,398,1462,1486]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="255">Alatae</emphasis>
as including “Plants glabrous or basally covered with simple hairs, with leaves subentire or more or less crenulate. Calyx with segments longer than the [calyx] tube. Corolla with segments shorter than the [corolla] tube, more or less ovate. Stamens inserted below the middle of the corolla tube. Carpels connate, attenuate into styles a little longer or a little shorter than the carpels. Scales sublinear or elongated-oval-sublinear. Seeds winged.” (translated from the original French in Raymond-Hamet 1933: 547–548).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5C43195D9430563F4F9D6A4EFC3556EF" blockId="0.[136,1452,1148,1867]" pageId="0" pageNumber="255">
Some 15 years later, 
<bibRefCitation id="386D64AC9430563F4E806A4EFD6B560A" author="Boiteau, P. &amp; Mannoni, O." box="[416,704,1635,1659]" pageId="0" pageNumber="255" pagination="57 - 58" refId="ref1953" refString="Boiteau, P. &amp; Mannoni, O. (1948 [octobre-decembre]) Les Kalanchoe (suite). [§ 4. Epidendrae; Kalanchoe porphyrocalyx (Baker) Baill. and Kalanchoe uniflora Raym. - Hamet (in the key).] (a suivre). Cactus (Paris) 17 - 18: 57 - 58 + two unnumbered figures." type="journal article" year="1948">Boiteau &amp; Mannoni (1948</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="386D64AC9430563F4DEB6A4EFCA9560A" author="Boiteau, P. &amp; Mannoni, O." box="[715,770,1635,1659]" pageId="0" pageNumber="255" pagination="9 - 14" refId="ref2022" refString="Boiteau, P. &amp; Mannoni, O. (1949 [janvier-mars]) Les Kalanchoe (suite). [Kalanchoe uniflora Raym. - Hamet; § 5. Scandentes; § (unnumbered) Bulbilliferae.] (a suivre). Cactus (Paris) 19: 9 - 14 + seven unnumbered figures." type="journal article" year="1949">1949</bibRefCitation>
) included 
<taxonomicName id="9BFC62DE9430563F4C546A49FB84560A" authorityName="Baillon" authorityYear="1885" baseAuthorityName="Baker" baseAuthorityYear="1883" box="[884,1071,1635,1659]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Kalanchoe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="0" pageNumber="255" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="porphyrocalyx">
<emphasis id="6E88C54F9430563F4C546A49FB84560A" box="[884,1071,1635,1659]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="255">K. porphyrocalyx</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="9BFC62DE9430563F4B446A49FB71560A" authorityName="Hamet" authorityYear="1910" baseAuthorityName="Stapf" baseAuthorityYear="1908" box="[1124,1242,1635,1659]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Kalanchoe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="0" pageNumber="255" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="uniflora">
<emphasis id="6E88C54F9430563F4B446A49FB71560A" box="[1124,1242,1635,1659]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="255">K. uniflora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in their 
<emphasis id="6E88C54F9430563F4A166A49FAE4560A" box="[1334,1359,1636,1659]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="255">K.</emphasis>
subsect. 
<emphasis id="6E88C54F9430563F4FA86AABFEAF56EF" box="[136,260,1670,1694]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="255">Epidendrae</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="386D64AC9430563F4E2B6AABFDF256EF" author="Boiteau, P. &amp; Mannoni, O." box="[267,601,1670,1694]" pageId="0" pageNumber="255" pagination="57 - 58" refId="ref1953" refString="Boiteau, P. &amp; Mannoni, O. (1948 [octobre-decembre]) Les Kalanchoe (suite). [§ 4. Epidendrae; Kalanchoe porphyrocalyx (Baker) Baill. and Kalanchoe uniflora Raym. - Hamet (in the key).] (a suivre). Cactus (Paris) 17 - 18: 57 - 58 + two unnumbered figures." type="journal article" year="1948">Boiteau &amp; Mannoni (1948: 57)</bibRefCitation>
, i.e., at the rank of subsection.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5C43195D9430563F4F9D6A84FEA55692" blockId="0.[136,1452,1148,1867]" pageId="0" pageNumber="255">
<bibRefCitation id="386D64AC9430563F4F9D6A84FE3C56B0" author="Gehrig, H. &amp; Gaussmann, O. &amp; Marx, H. &amp; Schwarzott, D. &amp; Kluge, M." box="[189,407,1705,1729]" pageId="0" pageNumber="255" pagination="827 - 835" refId="ref2119" refString="Gehrig, H., Gaussmann, O., Marx, H., Schwarzott, D. &amp; Kluge, M. (2001) Molecular phylogeny of the genus Kalanchoe (Crassulaceae) inferred from nucleotide sequences of the ITS- 1 and ITS- 2 regions. Plant Science 160: 827 - 835. https: // doi. org / 10.1016 / S 0168 - 9452 (00) 00447 - 7" type="journal article" year="2001">
Gehrig 
<emphasis id="6E88C54F9430563F4E306A84FEEA56B0" box="[272,321,1705,1729]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="255">et al</emphasis>
. (2001)
</bibRefCitation>
indicated that the two related species dealt with here, 
<taxonomicName id="9BFC62DE9430563F4CCB6A84FB0D56B0" authorityName="Baillon" authorityYear="1885" baseAuthorityName="Baker" baseAuthorityYear="1883" box="[1003,1190,1705,1729]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Kalanchoe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="0" pageNumber="255" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="porphyrocalyx">
<emphasis id="6E88C54F9430563F4CCB6A84FB0D56B0" box="[1003,1190,1705,1729]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="255">K. porphyrocalyx</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="9BFC62DE9430563F4BFD6A84FAFF56B0" authorityName="Hamet" authorityYear="1910" baseAuthorityName="Stapf" baseAuthorityYear="1908" box="[1245,1364,1705,1729]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Kalanchoe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="0" pageNumber="255" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="uniflora">
<emphasis id="6E88C54F9430563F4BFD6A84FAFF56B0" box="[1245,1364,1705,1729]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="255">K. uniflora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, form a single clade.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5C43195D9430563F4F9D6AC3FC3C573A" blockId="0.[136,1452,1148,1867]" pageId="0" pageNumber="255">
The winged seeds of members of this subgenus have yet to be recorded in other representatives of 
<taxonomicName id="9BFC62DE9430563F4BE36AC3FA9C5777" authorityName="Adanson" authorityYear="1763" box="[1219,1335,1774,1798]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Kalanchoe" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="0" pageNumber="255" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="6E88C54F9430563F4BE36AC3FA9C5777" box="[1219,1335,1774,1798]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="255">Kalanchoe</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and likely play a role in the dispersal and subsequent successful germination and establishment in suitable niches where these taxa occur, predominantly as epiphytes, in their natural habitat in 
<collectingCountry id="24EB59CD9430563F4C316B1EFC3F573A" box="[785,916,1843,1867]" name="Madagascar" pageId="0" pageNumber="255">Madagascar</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
